Tired of your life being put at risk by taxi drivers? Well... This might just be the solution to one of your problems. The SA taxi Industry is estimated to worth about R50-billion a year and many South Africans rely on it on a daily. The new technology will allow taxi bosses to stop their taxis remotely when the driver is overloading the vehicle or driving recklessly. Quickloc8 developed a monitoring and tracking system which it hopes will “bring integrity back to the taxi industry and promote transparency by giving power and control to the taxi owner and the associations”, says Mbavhalelo Mabogo, founder and CEO told Business Insider. "We install a device assembly in the taxi that can cut power if activated. We made sure it's possible only when the taxi is standing still or at safe speed." He added.   